{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK","doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout","doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller"]]},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/autoscroller\/duration"]}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"property","roleHeading":"Instance Property","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"duration","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"}],"externalID":"s:12UltraliteSDK12ScrollLayoutC12AutoScrollerC8durationSivp","title":"duration","modules":[{"name":"UltraliteSDK"}],"role":"symbol"},"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller\/duration"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The duration in milliseconds over which we animate text moving between positions. Value 0 indicates instantaneous movement rather than animation."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"duration"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":" { ","kind":"text"},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"set","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}]}]}],"references":{"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout/AutoScroller/duration":{"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"duration","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/autoscroller\/duration","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller\/duration","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The duration in milliseconds over which we animate text moving between positions. Value 0 indicates instantaneous movement rather than animation."}],"title":"duration","role":"symbol"},"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout/AutoScroller":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AutoScroller","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"AutoScroller"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"AutoScroller is a utility class to send a large known block of predfined text to the glasses to be smoothly scrolled."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This is simlar to what is seen on a teleprompter or in movie credits.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"This class was written using the ","type":"text"},{"code":"ScrollLayout","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" commands and is nothing more than a convience class."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Everything used this class can be written from the public SDK."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It scrolls the text much like a teleprompter would with basic commands to pause and resume the scrolling.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The duration (speed) of the scrolling can be modified while scrolling by seting the "},{"code":"duration","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" property.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It can support any language that the font supports.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"If the content is not known up front, or subject to change, this is the utility class will not work (use "},{"code":"LiveText","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance instead).","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/autoscroller","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller","title":"ScrollLayout.AutoScroller"},"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK":{"url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK","title":"UltraliteSDK","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this SDK to easily send text and images to your Vuxix smart glasses."}],"role":"collection"},"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ScrollLayout","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"When Ultralite.requestControl with a .scroll layout type .. this is the class you interate with to draw scrolling text to the screen.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Once the layout is .scrolled you must send one configure message to tell the layout how to setup.  It will setup the slice height and how many slices are visible.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"There are two supported modes: autoScroll on\/off","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"When autoScroll is true, the slices are automatically scrolled.  Subscribe to the delgate and listen for the scrolled callback, when you get it send another slice of text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"When autoScroll is false, you can drive the slices and how they look on the screen.  You can send all the slices at once or send one at a time and animate it onto the screen at the current time."}],"url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout","role":"symbol","title":"ScrollLayout","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ScrollLayout","kind":"identifier"}]}}}